.slide(data-slide='what-is-training-data', data-slide-nav='how-does-it-work')
  .explanation
    .container-fluid
      .row
        .col
          h2(data-i18n-str='training-data-title')
      .row
        .col-4
          p
            | Training data is the basis for a neural network to do what you want. It is usually a large set of sample data combined with the desired outputs (= the solutions, so to speak). Often a large part of the training data (e.g. 80%) is used to train the network, while the remaining part (e.g. 20%) is used to test the network and to check its performance / accuracy. Training data is very valuable, and luckily there are open databases like the MNIST database of handwritten digits that we used for this exhibit.
          p
            | For the Neural Numbers exhibit we used 70,000 images of handwritten digits (input) and the desired output (as a result):
          .figure
            img.img-fluid(src='assets/img/what-is-training-data-fig-1.png')
        .col-8
          p.lead
            | The training data is "cleaned up", ie all handwritten digits are centered in a 28x28 pixel field. Accordingly, your written digits are also prepared before the neural network can begin the analysis.
          .paint.columns#normalizepaint.mt-5
            .column
              .input.box.background
                .input-canvas-wrapper
                  canvas.drawcanvas
                .input-placeholder
                  span(data-i18n-str='ui-label-input-placeholder')
            .column
              .output.box
                .normalize-canvas-wrapper
                  canvas.normalizecanvas
                p.normalize-canvas-label(data-i18n-str='ui-label-output-normalized')
      .row
        .col
          .text-center
            a.button.button-back(href='#how-does-it-work', data-i18n-str='how-work-learn-back')

